    <folder name="En" id="id-5f7c7db882734778b8cad090422c271c">
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel" name="01 Read Me En" id="id-93b734aa61474cb3b28b6f42590db16b">
        <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-16ba6a9ddd494149bf8a4083bb35533a" textAlignment="1">
          <bounds x="36" y="48" width="727" height="829"/>
          <content>MODEL PURPOSE:
This model is a reference model of capabilities required for the effective operation of a software development company.

The model is designed for:

Maturity Assessment — identifying existing and missing capabilities.

Organizational Design — allocating responsibility for capabilities across departments.

Strategic Planning — determining development priorities for 1–3 years.

Roadmap Planning — sequencing the implementation of missing capabilities.

MODEL STRUCTURE:
The model is divided into two logical layers:

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DEVELOPMENT TEAM CAPABILITIES — capabilities directly related to software creation and delivery, which include:
• Product Management
• Development &amp; Delivery
• Operations &amp; Support
• Quality &amp; Security Management
• Team Leadership &amp; Administration
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CORPORATE CAPABILITIES — capabilities that ensure the company operates as a business, which include:
• Strategy &amp; Business Development
• Sales, Marketing &amp; CRM
• Corporate Governance
• Infrastructure &amp; Services
• BCP &amp; Risk Management
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

MODEL PRINCIPLES:
• Each capability is WHAT the organization should be able to do, regardless of HOW (processes) and BY WHOM (roles) it is implemented.
• Parent capabilities are decomposed into child capabilities through Composition relationships.
• The model is independent of specific technologies, methodologies, and organizational structures.

This model is available under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License.
To view a copy of this license, visit:
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

© 2026 Viktor Kopchenkov, https://kopchenkov.ru
When using, you must credit:
&quot;Author: Viktor Kopchenkov, Source: https://github.com/kopchenkov/software-development-reference-model&quot;</content>
        </child>
      </element>
